  "texts": [
    "It can be seen from Figure 4 that the full sample of stellar sources can be divided into two groups according to their T span values.",
    "One group has a time span within a few months (T span < 200 days) and the other group has a time span of approximately one year or several years (T span > 200 days), and the latter group is in the majority (the numbers of stellar sources of the two groups being 2,902 and 7,539, respectively).",
    "The behaviors of the stellar sources with different T span scales will be investigated in the following analysis.",
    "The dataset of the selected MRS time-domain sample of solar-like stars employed in this work is available online.",
    "Details of the dataset and the web link to the dataset can be found in Appendix E."
  ],
